Hypersion authors
=================

RenCopp <https://github.com/RenCopp>


Development assistance
----------------------

Hypersion was developed with substantial implementation help from
Anthropic's Claude (https://claude.com), in a long pair-programming
session covering the NNUE port, incremental accumulator updates, the
Finny refresh cache, search-margin retuning for NNUE, and other parts
of the engine. The architectural decisions and direction were RenCopp's;
Claude wrote and audited the code under that direction.


Acknowledgements
----------------

Hypersion's NNUE network files and inference algorithm are derived from
the Stockfish project (https://stockfishchess.org). Stockfish is the
work of the Stockfish team and many contributors; Hypersion benefits
from but is not affiliated with that project.

The bundled Fathom Syzygy probe (src/fathom/) was originally written by
Ronald de Man with substantial contributions by Basil Falcinelli, Jon
Dart, and others. See src/fathom/ for the upstream project and its
license terms.
